article.description: — Courvoisier McCauley had 16 points in Indiana State's 79-75 win over East Carolina on Monday night.
article.headline: Indiana State wins 79-75 against East Carolina
article.linkText: Indiana State wins 79-75 against East Carolina
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- — Courvoisier McCauley had 16 points in Indiana State's 79-75 win over East Carolina on Monday night. McCauley added seven rebounds for the Sycamores (4-0). Xavier Bledson scored 16 points while going 3 of 5 from the floor, including 2 for 4 from distance, and 8 for 10 from the line. Cooper Neese recorded 12 points and was 4 of 9 shooting, including 2 for 7 from distance, and went 2 for 3 from the line. Javon Small led the way for the Pirates (3-1) with 27 points, six rebounds and two steals. Kalib LaCount added 13 points and Brandon Johnson had 12 points, 13 rebounds and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
